:::


We will remove any subgroup that has less than 0.1 % of the total datapoints, i.e., 20 observations within a site, and then 1% less than overall, i.e., 200 observations. We will also drop "Light entering from outside during sleep", as it is very unevenly populated and dropped site levels will lead to issues later. For consistency with the glasses analysis, we will also drop `Electric light source outdoors`.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
hourly_data2 <-
  hourly_data |> 
  group_by(site, lightsource_primary) |> 
  mutate(n = n(),
         lightsource_primary = lightsource_primary |> 
           replace_when((n < 20 ) ~ NA)
           ) |> 
  group_by(lightsource_primary) |> 
  mutate(n = n(),
         lightsource_primary = lightsource_primary |> 
           replace_when((n < 200 ) ~ NA,
                        lightsource_primary == "Light entering from outside during sleep" ~ NA,
                        lightsource_primary == "Electric light source outdoors" ~ NA,),
         site = factor(site)
           )
```
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(nnet)
hourly_data3 <- hourly_data2 |> mutate(lightsource_primary = fct_drop(lightsource_primary))
model_lightsource_site <- multinom(
  lightsource_primary ~ site,
  data = hourly_data3
)
```

